ST. JOE PAPER COMPANY, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Roscoe O. WILLIAMS, Defendant-Appellant. No. 30629. United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. March 24, 1971. *694James H. Faulkner, Birmingham, Ala., for defendant-appellant. J. Michael Conaway, Walter R. Byars, Montgomery, Ala., for plaintiff-appellee.

Before GEWIN, BELL and ALDISERT,* Circuit Judges.

Of the Third Circuit, sitting by designation.

 PER CURIAM:

Affirmed. See Local Rule 21.**

See NLRB v. Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, 430 F.2d 966 (5th Cir. 1970).
